Now that we've fought in the arena, I have the thirst for victory.
Perkins, I need a victory! I have THE THIRST. I need it! I crave it!
You're scaring me, sir.
Good, you need a little more fear in your life. It builds character.
Let's now see if we can win a few more battles.
It's really hard to be as intelligent as I am. I have to think of everything.
Sir, we should also check in every once in a while to see if our formation has won battles against other outposts.
Great, sounds like a job for Sarge. I'll stay here and oversee our victory parade preparations. Perkins, how is the victory flag coming along?
My fingers are bleeding.
Well, sew faster and the pain will be over faster!
Lieutenant Morgan, sir? We've received an anonymous cable from another Outpost.
It's been a while since we've heard from anyone else out here. What's it say?
It's a challenge, sir. They're questioning our masculinity and saying some derogatory things about our mothers. They also question whether we are "soldier enough" to meet them in the arena.
Hmmm, let me see that note... Soldier enough?! Who do these chumps think they are? Wake the men and ready the defenses! We'll show them who's "soldier enough"!
After we've crushed everyone, we'll build a glorious statue honoring this victory!
Hahahahahaaaa! I mean, let's get that statue built.
We did it, Lieutenant. We won.
Yes, we've won once, but what about next time? We've got a long road ahead of us but I feel that with enough troops, time, and bullets, we can achieve total victory over everything!
That seems a bit megalomaniacal, sir.
Well done. Let's keep this momentum going.
These numbers are looking good! High command will be pleased.
Wow sir! You give me an ideal to strive for!
Este es el mapa. Para ir a Recoil Ridge, dirígete al sur y haz clic sobre él.
Venga, en marcha. Tenemos un largo viaje por delante. Haz clic en el botón del mapa.
Sólo tienes que hacer clic sobre la casa para regresar a tu puesto.
Haz clic sobre el botón de "Aleatorio" que se encuentra en la parte inferior de la pantalla. O puedes visitar a algún amigo y saquear su puesto para robarle preciosos recursos.
Jabalíes
Jabalíes
Jabalíes
Jabalíes
Haz clic sobre el botón Construcción y luego en el Punto de recogida.
Ahora haz clic sobre la mercancía para recogerla. ¡Venga, ábrela!
Cuando el refugio esté completo, haz clic en él para meter a la gente. Así podrán trabajar en el punto de recogida.
¡Para gestionar los edificios necesitamos alojamiento! Haz clic en Construcción y crea un refugio.
Haz clic en los soldados de tu inventario para añadirlos a la batalla.
A continuación, haz clic en el botón Luchar.
Haz clic en el campo de entrenamiento y luego "Entrenar" para formar un soldado.
Haz clic en el botón "Rápido" para terminar el soldado.
¡Haz clic en un grupo de asaltantes para echarlos de nuestra tierra!
Asaltantes exploradores
Asaltantes exploradores
pero me has dejado claro que he descuidado mi deber como ingeniero civil.
Morgan, la mina de hierro es estupenda,
¿Vas a instalar un sistema de alcantarillas? Dime que sí, por favor.
No, voy a transformar materialmente la topografía local, induciendo así el desarrollo de una infraestructura de transporte que aumentará la eficiencia del traslado de materia prima.
¿Perdona?
Capitán, encontrarás los caminos en la pestaña Decoración del menú Construcción.
Voy a construir caminos de tierra.
Los camiones tratarán de seguir las carreteras que traces. Tiene más sentido que cruzar la tierra sin más.
¡Mira qué bien van!
El campo de tiro está listo. Haz clic en él para empezar a disparar.
Si alguien resulta herido, haz clic en el hospital para empezar a curarlos.
Cuando estés listo, haz clic en la bandera y entra en la refriega.
Oh...
But no, the Annual Winter Jubilee Charity Drive for Children is startin' up, and figured you folks might want to chip in.
Yeah, I feel like we're gonna be a "maybe", but the kind of "maybe" that sorta means "no"?
We try to encourage folks with some friendly competition. Biggest donor gets a prize.
I'm in.
Tradition is, folks just donate 'em right back. It's really more a formality than anything else–
I think the raptor is staring at me with its cold dead eyes, but it's hard to see past its glowing nose.
colt
Keep donating troops, we will destroy those children with kindness!
You're so damn charitable, everyone will fear your name.
Ramsey insisted we put bows on the tanks to make them look festive.
Guns are like toys with consequences.
Purrface needs toys too, you know.
Keep donating! Make our enemies weep!
You're almost there! Let's show Sheriff Colt how damn charitable we are.
These toys are a burden to the environment.
So close! I can taste victory, and it's almost as good as whiskey.
I was the one who snuck the bees into Perkins' tent… don't tell anyone.
Anyone want to arm wrestle?
The point is to NOT remember.
Y'all are the worst friends a fella could ask for, but at least yer friends.
I said I wouldn't take part in libations, but I never said I wouldn't dance!
I just hope all my broken robots are in some kind'a robot heaven.
We're not allowed in the hall. But nobody said anything about raptors in disguises!
No, Floyd, I do not want to dance!
Captain Pike? What are you doing up here? Enjoying the winter of the Northern Frontier?
I wish that were the case, Lieutenant. While my home country isn't exactly warm, this type of winter is something we're not used to. I'm afraid we all may freeze to death without your assistance.
I'm sure we can give you a hand. And by "we" I mean not me.
Floyd! Why are you never around when I actually want you to be? Help Captain Pike here not freeze to death.
Have you tried dressing in layers?
You're not making it easy to like you.
So, you really think boots are that important? I always thought of them as simply a means to keep my feet off the ground.
That's why you keep needing our help, Pike. Boots make the man. Without a good pair of boots on your feet, you face certain defeat. I'm not trying to make a cute pun either. I mean it.
Also I hate puns.
Most intriguing, Lieutenant. I've always enjoyed a good pun myself.
Hey Perkins! Radio Captain Pike and let him know we'll be arriving at his port shortly with his winter gear.
Yes sir. I'll let him know immediately.
Wait a second, did Pike post a few ships outside his port to meet us? What am I looking at here?
They look like Sovereign ships, Lieutenant. Looks like they're about to attack Port City.
Perfect! For once, we have the element of surprise!
Where do all these holidays come from anyway?
These boots are excellent, Lieutenant. What do we owe you for compensation?
Under normal circumstances, this is the point where I would try to con you out of a bunch of your money. But seeing as it's the season for giving, consider it a Festivus gift.

Festivus? I assume this is a winter tradition of yours? We have one of those as well we call 'Boxes Day'. People are encouraged to buy their friends and family gifts, and to put them in boxes as a surprise.
Man, it's great to be back at the Outpost. I'm tired of always rushing to the aid of others. I say we impose some sort of base-wide non-interference policy. We can't be the police of everything.
It looks like some Sovereign ships followed us back to the Outpost, sir. Should I tell them we don't want to fight them and to leave us alone?
I mean, you can try, but I don't think they're gonna listen. I guess there's always the extremely slim chance they want to give us gifts for that Boxes Day thing Pike mentioned...
Maybe they'll leave if we turn off the lighthouse, like no one's home?
Tell him to shoot anyone that tries to wake me up.
That took care of 'em, Lieutenant. I don't see anymore ships in the harbor, at least.
That's good news, Ramsey. OK, are we safe for a few minutes? Can I go lie down now?
We appear to be, yeah.
Great. Make sure nobody bothers me for a while, and have Perkins stand guard outside my bedroom.
Did you enjoy your nap, sir?

Yeah I did, surprisingly. It doesn't look like anything caught fire while I was asleep, either. And now I see Captain Pike approaching. Great. I wonder what catastrophe he needs help avoiding this time.
Lieutenant Morgan! My men and I wanted to thank you for your recent generosity, so we brought you all some Boxes Day gifts. We hope you enjoy them!
Oh wow, is that it? No life threatening problems, or hostile factions after you?
Well, there was one other thing. It's a Boxes Day tradition to celebrate the times with copious amounts of food and alcohol!
Boxes Day sounds amazing!
Happy Holidays, Outpost!

Really Ramsey, I think I can take care of a few boars. I been huntin' boars in these parts for most of my life.
Yeah, but I'm not worried about running into boars.
This guy better watch out!
See Ramsey? Nothin' to worry about. Now, back to what we came here for. I'm seein' some more of those tracks and they're goin' back toward your Outpost.
Back? This thief must be a master of stealth. Is there anything else you're seeing?
No, we should probably get back now. No point in us standin' out here in the freezin' cold. We still got a thief to catch!
Alright Sheriff, where are the tracks headed this time?
Looks like they're headed this way, towards the shore. They seem to stop at the end of this dock. You know where any of these ships were headed?
Yes sir. Those ships go through the Reef Bandit fishing grounds territory.
Well, you might want to go out there and have a talk with 'em. Aren't those Reef Bandits known for stealin'?
I wonder if they have any winter celebrations...
Seriously? We've met him like, what, twice?
Perkins? Do you have those flash cards we got from the translator, Karin? Try talking to the Chief, see what he knows.
The Chief doesn't know of any of his people stealing items from the Outpost. None of his people have been near it recently, according to him.
Well that's just swell. I guess we should head back now.
He also said he's insulted he wasn't invited to the celebration.
Ok we're back. Is anyone seeing anything? It doesn't look like the entire Outpost was looted while we were away, but everyone should check their stuff.
I found some more tracks. Looks like they're headin' this way, towards Ramsey's shack.
Oh no! I gotta make sure Mr. Purrface is OK!
Mr. Purrface looks fine, except… Wait a second. Why does Mr. Purrface have one of my gloves in his mouth? And what's all that stuff under your recliner?
Oh great. Looks like we found the culprit. Sorry everyone. Mr. Purrface was probably just trying to find me some Festivus gifts.
My flask has cat fur all over it.
So wait, it was an actual cat burglar?
Once again, sorry about Mr. Purrface. He doesn't know any better. He's just a good little kitty that likes shiny things.
Mrrrow?
See? He's really sorry too. Who's a fluffy little guy?
Well, this was certainly an interesting Festivus.
Perkins, ¿cómo van las compras para estas fiestas?
¡Perkins!
Ehh... aún no... he comenzado...
Genial, quiero que cambies ese costoso regalo que me tienes preparado por una codorniz en un manzano.
¿Una codorniz en un manzano?
¿Y porqué no? Manzanas, mascota y cena cuando me canse de cuidarla. ¡Como tu comandante, mi regalo debe ser tu prioridad número uno!
Por supuesto señor.
Perkins! Have you started your Festivus gift gathering yet?
Er... Not yet...
Good, because I want to change the undoubtedly large and expensive present you were already planning to get me.  I want a quail in an apple tree!
A quail... in an apple tree, sir?
Why not? I get apples, I get a pet, and I get a quail dinner when I finally get tired of cleaning up after it! As your commanding officer, I expect my gift to get top priority, of course!
Of course, sir.
I guess I'll have to give him the socks next year...
I know. I'm such a benevolent boss.
Ah, one of the nicest things about having authority is the ability to abuse it!
Does that mean you're satisfied?
Well, the quail is kind of scrawny, and the apples could be a little redder...  But in the spirit of Festivus, I'll reduce your punishment for your incompetence by 50%!
That's very generous of you, sir.
Supongo que le guardaré los calcetines para el próximo año...
Al parecer no soy el único que está al acecho de esa codorniz...
Lo sé, soy un jefe muy bondadoso.
Ah, ¡una de las mejores ventajas de tener autoridad es poder de abusar de ella!
¿Eso significa que te das por satisfecho?
Pues la codorniz está raquítica y las manzanas podrían estar un poco más rojas... Sin embargo, en época festiva el castigo por tu incompetencia lo reduzco a la mitad.
¡Que generoso eres señor!
Vamos a ver, ¿quién más esta en mi lista de época festiva...?
Hmm, el sargento quiere unas campanillas para el collar del señor Bigotes.
Let's see, who else is on my Festivus wish list...?
Hmm, the Sarge wants some bells for Mr. Purrface's collar.
Jingle bells are festive... in small doses, anyway.
Now he's carrying a dead rat! Isn't that the cutest?
Oooh, Mr. Purrface! Those bells look soooo adorable on you! Are you enjoying your new jingly collar, my little snookie-wookums?
Meow!
It's definitely more than I usually get.
Las campanillas son festivas... en pequeñas dosis.
¡Mira como lleva esa rata muerta! ¡Que monada!
¡Señor Bigotes! Que bien se te ven esas campanillas. ¿Te gusta tu nuevo collar? ¡Que mono que eres!
¡Miau!
Ahhh, el Señor Bigotes le dice gracias al especialista. ¡Que ternura!
Esto es más de lo que me esperaba.
Floyd quiere darle refugio a los jabalíes salvajes. Se están muriendo de hambre por el frío invierno.
Necesita que... ejem... "arrear a esos hambrientos y furiosos jabalíes salvajes hacia nuestro puesto para su propia protección, de una forma amistosa y humana".
Los puedo dejar inconscientes y decirle a Floyd que están durmiendo la siesta.
Floyd wants to shelter boars that are starving because of the harsh winter conditions.
He needs to... oh... "herd strong, long-tusked, hunger crazed boars into the outpost for their own protection, in a friendly and humane fashion."
Maybe I'll just knock them unconscious and tell Floyd they're napping.
No, Morgan! Put down that shotgun this instant!
Is it just me, or do these boars seem a bit... sluggish?
Ah... It must be the cold...
Hmm. Yes. I suppose you must be right. Excellent work, Perkins! This will be a very happy Festivus for our porcine friends, which makes me very happy indeed!
A pen full of boars? Great! I was just planning Festivus dinner!
Me gustaba la carne antes, cuando ignoraba de dónde salía.
¡Morgan no! ¡Baja esa escopeta de inmediato!
¿Soy yo o esos jabalíes se ven un poco... lentos?
Ah... seguro que es el frío...
Hmm, si, supongo que llevas razón. ¡Muy buen trabajo Perkins! Estas van a ser unas excelentes festividades para nuestros amigos porcinos, ¡lo cual me pone muy feliz!
¿Un redil lleno de jabalíes? ¡Excelente! ¡Estaba preparando la cena para las festividades!
El sheriff Colt necesita ayuda con el jubileo de invierno... Supongo que esa es la manera que tienen de celebrar las festividades.
Será una fiesta enorme y quiere tener una especie de zona anti vip aquí en el puesto... ¡significa que necesitamos nuevas decoraciones!
A little holiday cheer helps everyone!
Ehh, I'll take it.
Well, now! This place is lookin' right festive! This is gonna be one heck of a Winter Jubilee!
Did somebody say "festive"?  Is there dinner? Is someone making me dinner?

Oh, I'm sorry, son; the Jubilee's for us frontier folk only. The Empire what subjugated us and stole our heritage ain't exactly welcome.  But I'll tell ya what: when the party's over, y'all can help clean up. You can even suck the barbeque sauce off the rib bones if ya want!
Ehh, de acuerdo.
¡Muy bien! ¡Ahora este lugar se ve perfecto para las festividades! ¡Este será un gran jubileo de invierno!
¿Escuché a alguien decir "festivo"? ¿Hay comida? ¿Quién esta haciendo mi cena?
Lo siento hijo, el jubileo es para fronterizos. El imperio que nos subyugó y acabó con nuestras costumbres no es bienvenido. Sin embargo puedes venir cuando hayamos acabado para que ayudes a limpiar.
Zoey quiere ver nieve en las festividades. Pero la nieve de por aquí es arenosa y sucia.
Tengo dos opciones: subir a la montaña arriesgándome a morir congelado sepultado bajo alguna avalancha... o probar la máquina experimental del clima de Floyd.
... Creo que estaré más seguro en la montaña.
Zoey wants some snow for Festivus. But the snow around here is all sandy and dirty and gross.
I'll have to either go up into the mountains and get some snow, risking frostbite and avalanches while lugging around giant coolers... or try out Floyd's experimental weather machine.
… I think I'm safer with the frostbite and avalanches.
I think the whole planet is safer, actually...
Creo que el mundo entero es un lugar más seguro...
Ya estoy aquí... es hora de llenar el refrigerador. Espero que haya suficiente.
Oh oh. Espero que sea el viento y no el aliento de un enorme y furioso animal detrás mio...
Well, I'm here...  Time to start filling the coolers. Hopefully this will be enough.
Uh oh. I hope that was just the wind, and not the grunting of a very large animal right behind me...
I must've interrupted the Bigfoot Festivus!
This is the most festive Zoey disaster ever.
Wowee! Look at all the snow! This is great! Come on, Perkins! Let's make a snow-tank!
A... snow-tank?
Sure! And I can even outfit it so that it'll actually move and shoot flame without meltin'! Lemme just get the exoskeleton ready...
I think I'll go before this gets out of control...
¡Debo haber interrumpido las festividades de los Pie grande!
¡Pie grandes! ¡Y al parecer no están contentos!
Este es el desastre mas festivo de todos.
¡Viva! ¡Mira toda esa nieve! ¡Esto es fantástico! Vamos Perkins, ¡hay que hacer un tanque de nieve!
Un... ¿tanque de nieve?
¡Claro! Y puedo hacer una coraza para que podamos disparar fuego sin que se derrita! Voy a hacer el exoesqueleto de inmediato...
Creo que mejor me voy antes de que esto se salga de control...
¿Qué querrán Taro, Daro y como se llame el otro? Son niños. A todos los niños les gustan los juguetes ¿no?
Si, claro que es así. Tal vez pueda ahorrarme algo de oro si los hago yo mismo.
Though I'm kind of impressed by their ingenuity.
Wow! Look at these neat toys!
Bet you're going to have a lot of fun playing with them, huh?
You bet! This telescope will make a great barrel and we can use the spring on the pogo stick as a launcher and the marbles will make cool ammo and it'll be the best cannon EVER!
… Did I just arm a group of kids?
¡Que ganas tengo de ver sus pequeñas caras!
Me sorprende un poco su ingenuidad.
¡Que juguetes más bonitos!
Apuesto a que os vais a divertir mucho con ellos ¿no?
¡Por supuesto! De este telescopio podemos hacer un cañón usando el resorte del palo pogo y como munición tenemos las canicas. ¡El mejor regalo de todos!
¿Cómo he podido armar un grupo de niños?
Cassidy no ha podido dormir bien ultimamente porque los animales alrededor de Recoil Ridge hacen mucho ruido.
Tal vez sean los grillos o las ranas, o algún otro animal fácil de... ¿a quién engaño?
Cassidy's been having trouble getting to sleep lately because of animals making noise around Recoil Ridge.
Maybe it's just crickets, or frogs, or something else that'll be easy to... Oh, who am I kidding?
There's not a lot I wouldn't do for a good night's sleep!
Ramsey! You stop chasing the poor kid RIGHT NOW!
Oh, Perkins, last night was just heavenly! Thank you so much! You did wonderful!
No problem, ma'am! Just let me know if you need me again!
Cassidy? Perkins?! "Last night"? "Heavenly"? "Did wonderful"?!?
Ah, sir! Let me explain... Sarge, you're starting to scare me; don't look at me like that...! Sarge, please, put away the gun!
¡Mi reino por una buena noche de sueño!
¡Ramsey! ¡Deja de perseguir a ese pobre chico YA MISMO!
Oh, Perkins, ¡que noche! ¡Mil gracias! ¡Fue fantástico!
¡Con mucho gusto! ¡Cuando me necesites de nuevo no dudes en hacérmelo saber!
¿Cassidy? ¡¿Perkins?! ¿"Noche"? ¿"Mil gracias"? ¿¡¿"Fantástico"?!?
Ah si, señor, déjame explicarte... sargento, empiezas a asustarme. ¡No me mires así!... Sargento, ¡por favor guarda tu arma!
¡Al fin es mi turno! ¡Ahora puedo hacer algo para mí! Pero... ¿qué quiero? Hmmm.
Siempre me gustaron las festividades... Y parece que la fiesta en Recoil Ridge fue todo un éxito... ¡Ya está! ¡Quiero unas festividades como deben ser aquí mismo!
Finally, it's my turn!  I get to do something for me! But... what do I want?  Hmmmm.
Well, I've always loved Festivus... And Recoil Ridge's party seemed like a lot of fun... That's it! I want a good old fashioned Festivus celebration right here!
When I get my own gift, I never have to wonder if I'll like it.
Pass me a third piece of that tolerable pie...
Perkins, my boy, this truly is a festive Festivus! A marvelous atmosphere!
It reminds me of my holidays back home! *sniff*
This dinner is great! Thanks, Perkins!
Meh, it's tolerable.
This is my REAL Festivus gift!
Cuando me doy mi propio regalo no tengo que adivinar si me va a gustar o no.
Dame una tercera porción de ese mediocre pastel...
Perkins, chico, ¡esta es una fiesta de verdad! ¡Que atmósfera tan maravillosa!
¡Me recuerda a las fiestas de mi hogar! *sniff*
¡Esta cena estuvo deliciosa! ¡Gracias Perkins!
Hmm, mediocre diría yo.
¡Este es mi regalo real de las festividades!
El mayor Taos dice que tiene problemas con algunos asaltantes pero que esta muy ocupado con el festín de Dawnbringer como para ocuparse de él.
El festín de  Dawnbringer... Supongo que los asaltantes también tienen sus festividades. En fin, es la hora de reunir unos soldados y ayudar a Taos...
Elder Taos says some renegade Raiders are making trouble, and he's too busy with the Dawnbringer Feast to deal with them.
Dawnbringer Feast... So I guess the Raiders have their own Festivus. Well, time to grab a few soldiers and help the Elder out...
Hey, it's the Skinny Beast's slave boy!
Even the nice Raiders scare me...
Now the preparations for the Dawnbringer Feast can continue without distraction or interference. You have done well.
What is the Dawnbringer Feast all about?

It is a winter celebration to enjoy the bounty of the past year, while coaxing the sun out of hiding for the next. We light bonfires, eat much meat, and tell stories of times of old. As a champion of our people, you would be an honored guest.
Oh, thanks! What time should I stop by?
We will begin in two nights, at dawn, by decorating our tents with the entrails of our enemies, followed by pit fighting.
Umm...  I'll see about getting leave for that...
Que mala suerte que no pueda enviar al temible bestia raquítica...
Incluso los asaltantes más gentiles me asustan...
Ahora podemos seguir con las preparaciones del festín de Dawnbringer sin interferencias. Gracias.
¿Qué es eso del festín de Dawnbringer?
Es una fiesta de invierno en la que celebramos las cosechas del año pasado. Encendemos fogatas, comemos carne y contamos historias. Como héroe que eres, sería nuestro honor que asistieras.
Oh, ¡gracias! ¿A qué hora debería venir?
Comenzaremos en dos noches, al atardecer. Decoramos las tiendas con las entrañas de nuestros enemigos y en seguida habrá una pelea a puño limpio.
Hmmm.. Veré si puedo hacerme con un permiso para ello...
Percival necesita provisiones para una expedición que adelanta en las montañas del norte.
El teniente Morgan cree que si le ayudamos nos dará acceso a más artefactos antiguos... En todo lo deberíamos ayudar, ¡son las festividades!
Percival needs some food supplies for an expedition he's making in the mountains up north.
Lieutenant Morgan thinks if we help him, he'll share more Ancient artifacts with us. But it's the holidays! We should help him anyway!
Funny how MY rations are usually some kind of gruel...
Am I the only one who'd prefer the smoothie machine...?
Ah, this should keep my team and myself full and energetic! Pass on my thanks to your Lieutenant!
No problem... Um, if you don't mind me asking, what are you looking for this time?

A fascinating ruin described in an Ancient scroll I just found! It holds an artifact that's either an infinite energy source... or an infinite smoothie machine. The translation was unclear on that point.
Es curioso como mis raciones son siempre un tipo de gacha...
¿Soy la única persona en el mundo que hubiera preferido una licuadora...?
¡Con esto tendré fuerzas para rato! ¡Dale las gracias de mi parte al teniente!
Con gusto. Hmmm, si no te importa que te pregunte, ¿qué estás buscando ahora?

¡Unas fascinantes ruinas que describen unos rollos que acabo de encontrar! En su interior se encuentra un artefacto que puede ser una fuente infinita de energía... o una licuadora sin fin. La traducción no lo dejó claro.
Yenkcha quiere capturar y convertir en mascota a un legendario velociraptor que tiene la nariz roja y al que llaman Ruddock.
El teniente Morgan quiere que la ignore pero ella también merece unas felices festividades... eh, ¡y también un banquete Dawnbringer! ¡Ella hace de este lugar un sitio mucho más entretenido!
Yenkcha wants to capture a legendary Raptor with a red nose called Ruddock as a pet.
Lieutenant Morgan wants me to ignore her, but heck, she deserves a happy Festivus - er, Dawnbringer Feast - too! Besides, she makes life here a lot more entertaining!
He has a very shiny nose - I could even say it glows!
Heck, even I can't believe I actually did it!

Perkins, I just got a message from Yenkcha thanking me for the "generous gift" I brought her, and that she'll tell all her suitors about how brave I was to face Ruddock the Red Nosed Raptor in deadly single combat.
You don't happen to know anything about this, do you?
Me, sir? Going into the wilderness and hunting a huge, hostile Raptor? Do you really think I'm the type to do that?
Hmmm. Good point. Forget it, then.
Tiene una nariz muy brillante. ¡Diría que brilla!
¡No puedo creer que yo lo haya hecho!

Perkins, acabo de recibir un mensaje de Yenkcha en el cual me agradece "el generoso regalo" que le compré. Además dice que le ha contado a todos sus pretendientes lo valiente que he sido al enfrentarme a Ruddock, el raptor de nariz roja, en un encuentro mortal.
¿De esto no sabes nada no?
¿Yo señor? ¿Ir a la selva para cazar a un velociraptor? ¿Yo? ¿De verdad crees que sería capaz?
Hmmm, buen punto. Olvídalo.
Oh, ¡no te he olvidado capitán!
¡Tengo una sopresa extra para tí! He tenido que tocar muchas puertas y pedir muchos favores ¡pero ya casi está listo!
Espero que nadie se entere de lo espectacular que es mi regalo y trate de robarme la idea antes de que te lo de a tí.
Oh, I haven't forgotten you, Captain!
I got something extra special for you! I had to pull a lot of strings and call in a lot of favors, but it's almost ready!
I sure hope no one gets wind of how great this gift is and tries to steal it before I can give it to you...
I have to learn to stop tempting fate like that.
Ramsey truly knows what's important in life!
Whew! Now that they're gone, I can finally give you your gift, Captain: nanopods!
Nanopods?! How the hell did you get your hands on nanopods? And why did I ask for a quail in an apple tree when I could've asked for nanopods??
Well, I've been saving them up, and I wanted them for a special occasion. But the Captain's done such a good job keeping us alive and all, and, well...
No matter! This is a fine gift for the Captain!
Sure is! Have a happy holiday, Captain!
Here's to another year of food, friends, and blowing up Rebels with really big tanks!
Debo aprender a dejar de probar mi suerte de esta manera.
¡Ramsey sabe de verdad qué es lo primordial en la vida!
¡Al fin se han ido! Aquí tienes tu regalo capitán: ¡nanopods!
¿Cómo conseguiste nanopods? ¿Cómo fue que pedí una codorniz en un manzano y no nanopods?
¡¿Nanopods?!
Los he estado guardando desde hace un tiempo para una ocasión especial, pero como el capitán nos ha cuidado de esta forma pues...
¡Que importa! ¡Este es un gran regalo para el capitán!
¡Claro que si! ¡Felices fiestas capitán!
¡A la salud de otro año lleno de comida, amigos y acabar con los rebeldes usando enormes tanques!
Haz clic en el botón "Mover" para reubicar el cobertizo. Si oyes alguna queja, haz clic en el botón "Vender".
¡Los zombis son patrañas!
¡Los zombis son patrañas!
¡En el puesto! ¡Me han atacado!
¡Zombis!
¡Imposible! Biológicamente no tiene ningún sentido. ¿De dónde viene su energía? ¿Cómo la pueden obtener de materiales crudos para…
¿Zombis?
¡Salieron de la nada y me atacaron! ¿Qué es lo que está pasando?
¡Acabo de matar a un poco de zombis!
Primero hay que calmarse y proteger a los civiles. Ramsey, investiga qué es lo que esta pasando.
Esto es absurdo. ¡Los zombis son apenas un mito! ¡No es posible darle vida a un tejido muerto! ¡Ni los nanopods pueden darle vida a los muertos!
Di lo que quieras Floyd pero yo sé lo que vi. Son zombis y si estás tan seguro de que no existen, ¿por qué no vienes con nosotros a investigar?
Es exactamente lo que voy a hacer. ¡Ahora veremos a qué nos estamos enfrentando!
¡Déjalo a la ciencia!
¡Zombis!
¡Mira!
¡De sus heridas sale sangre! Eso significa que sus sistemas circulatorios están en pleno funcionamiento y por ende NO SON ZOMBIS.
¿Y entonces qué son?
Atrapa a ese que está atontado y llévalo a mi laboratorio. Ya veremos de qué se trata.
Sé lo que es un zombi cuando lo veo.

Aunque si bien es cierto, tú eres el científico y al final seguro que terminarás muerto. Adelante con tus experimentos.

Pude extraer estos. Parecen nanopods pero opacos y negros.

… ¿qué fue lo que nunca pudiste decirme teniente?
Espera, ¿Perkins no es un zombi?
¡Perkins! ¡Quítate ese ridículo disfraz! ¡Ve y límpiate! Aquí tienes tu cepillo.
Dr. Harris, your little pet project is running 'amuck outside.
…which one?
Some ancient tech. I think you called 'er Experiment X17?
What did you do to her?
Experiment X17?!
Nothin', except almost getting blasted a few years backwards from those lasers. This ain't on me.
What did 'I' do to her?!
Hmm. I always entertained the possibility of Experiment X17 escaping my control. And ordinary weapons won't harm this ancient construct.
Well, L.T and the rest of us, we're over our heads. Let's go to i17. Maybe they can help us.
i17? Might as well ask a bunch of grad students for help...
I believe I was the one who wrote up those blueprints...
Dr. Harris, I didn't think I'd see you again.
I was hoping I wouldn't.
Trust me, if I wanted someone to alphabetize my microbial slides you'd be the first one I'd call.
It's about as far as your scientific prowess will take you.
C'mon, can't you guys stop fussin' at each other? We've got a killer ancient tech on the loose and none of the weapons we got can even scratch the thing.
In our archives we have blueprints for a weapon that could potentially defeat such a creature. Unfortunately, we don't have the materials available.
How hard can it be? What do you need?
Well, first off, we'll need a jet engine...
The ethanol injectors are goin' in fine, Floyd! We'll be done in no time!
That's wonderful Zoey! It's so rare that we have the opportunity to act in a purely benevolent manner, helping to undo some of the damage that's been done to our natural world.
Sir! Spiderwasps! In the mine! They're attacking the workers!
Sorry Floyd, looks like we gotta do some damage to the natural world.
Still, it's nice knowing our intentions were pure.
I try to maintain a positive outlook. I REALLY do.
Alright, what's done is done. Let's finish getting the ethanol injectors installed, and see if we can't minimize any further damage.
Will do, Floyd! But I feel like I should warn ya, the fight mighta caused some damage ta the local fault lines. I wouldn't be surprised if there were earthquakes or somethin'.
Nor would I, Zoey. Nor would I.
Hey Floyd, remember when I said we mighta caused a coupla earthquakes?
Are we about to be crushed to death?
I mean, it's possible an' all, but it looks like a quake opened up a Spiderwasp nest ta the south, so there's a real good chance they'll run all over every village nearby… and the Outpost.
Well, at least we're not getting crushed.
And if the ethanol doesn't work, I'm just going to scream for a few hours and then move on.
Well, that was a heck of a disaster. An' we still haven't figured out a way to keep the Spiderwasps from goin' wild. Sorry, Floyd.
Zoey, we're not dead, we're not paralyzed by a poison, AND we managed to get the ethanol injectors installed and working.
Sure, we uncovered a massive Spiderwasp nest and riled up the hordes of giant insects within, but I'm going to go ahead and call this one a win.

Let's break it down. Someone is feeding Intel to the Rebels. We've found accurate intel, but it tends to be vague. Then we've found extremely specific stuff, some of which is entirely accurate, and some of which has been fudged to make us look like monsters.

Ashe has told us whoever fudged the intel did it on purpose. But the Rebels BELIEVED them, even though it was pretty far fetched. So it stands to be reasoned that this person is someone who is trusted both by us AND the rebellion.
Either the Rebels have an existing relationship with this person, or the person is so well placed, that they couldn't help but take them seriously. Who could that possibly be?
Installation 17? Maybe someone out there wanted to cut a deal?
I don't know I guess so, hey Mister Perkins, how come you're asking us instead of going there and finding out?
Hard to find an audience for long-winded monologues these days.
Whew, it was some work getting those files back to the Outpost, but I'm ready to dive in!
This is going to take all night... guess we better get started.
I'll need some kale juice to get me through this.
Kale... juice? Why not just some coffee?
Perkins, I am ashamed of you. Coffee is a stimulant. Coffee is a DRUG.
So you're not okay with coffee, but you're okay with putting experimental drugs IN Lieutenant Morgan's coffee? Okay. That makes sense.

What does coffee contain? Adenosine! What is adenosine? It's an inhibitory neurotransmitter that plays a role in energy regulation. Coffee blocks the adenosine receptors, dysregulating our natural energy cues! It's highly addictive!
Caffeine can also cause ulcers, miscarriage, and death!
Okay, okay! We'll make the kale juice. THEN can we get to the archives?
I haven't had this much fun since my days of middle school experimentation with dry ice.
Sometimes, I really, really hate knowing things.
I can barely keep my eyes open, and we haven't found anything useful.
Installation 17 was incredibly thorough. Before the collapse of the Empire, there would have been no chance of a leak.
Even now, I'd say it's highly unlikely any of their employees would have had the breathing room to become an informant.
Well, that's a disturbing revelation.
I think we've come to the same conclusion, and I have to agree. It couldn't have been an employee of Installation 17. At least, one outside a leadership role.
So, IF the leak came from Installation 17, that leaves either Archibald himself, or Aurora. And seeing as how we work with one, and saved the other, it's an unlikely, but terrifying, possibility.
Sir, we're being attacked by Rebels.
Ramsey, I heard you say something but your lips weren't moving. Are you practicing ventriloquism now? And can you teach me? How did you do the "buh" sound in "being?"
No, I say that phrase so often I recorded it. See?
Ah, then never mind about the ventriloquism. That was just to test you.
Smooth cover, Morgan...
I did it! And my hands are only a little burned!
Captain, I'm not usually one for celebrations and parties, unless whiskey is involved.
In fact, I banned parties after the last one caused wide scale riots, but we've made it to level 60.
L.T, 60 is great but 65 is even better! And if we can get there, I've got somethin' special planned!
Well we better hurry and level up while we can. As we get stronger, so does everyone else who's trying to kill us...
Getting killed would be really inconvenient right now.
I guess the little trooper guy is kind of cute.
Well, we did it, Captain. We made it to level 65.
We've survived raiders, silver wolves, rebels, mammoths, ninjas, and creatures who were driven to homicidal rage by poisonous gases.
...Just so you know, I haven't forgiven you for that last one, Floyd.
Will this commemorative statue that Zoey and I have been working on alleviate your ill will toward me?
It depends, is it a statue of me?
No. It's a memorial to represent our progress as an Outpost and our commitment to battle head on whatever struggles we may face in the future.
Then forget it.
I think it looks pretty cool! Look at the size of that tank!
The gall of him!
At least Trotbeck isn't full of crazy hippies.
That's the first thing they teach us in Basic Training.
I detest violence.
You should ESPECIALLY not trust a hippy with a farmhouse.
But you just destroyed our weapons facility...
Perkins v. The Sandworm
Perkins' Parasite?
They must've gotten riled up by the signals secreted by the sandworm in times of distress.
I don't care how they got here! I just want them gone.
Maybe I can get some samples while I'm here?
I wish Perkins was here so I could kill him.
Oh no, more sandworms!
Assassins! They murdered him!
No, no! It's been a mistake! We didn't kill him! He just fell over dead while we were about to sign the peace treaty! Did anyone know if he had a heart condition?
A heart condition that looks a lot like an arrow in the back? Oh god. He WAS assassinated.
Just when everything was going so well… I should've known.
Troops, prepare yourselves! Get to your battle stations!
Assassinating someone at peace talks is seven years bad luck...
I don't have much left to give...
Someone really has it out for us, you know?
Honestly, can you blame them?

I've dedicated my whole life to fighting this rebellion. I've had to trudge through swamps and harsh deserts and watch my best friends die of curable infections and amputations. I've starved for weeks and had to drink things you don't even want to know exist.

I've lost my faith, my hope, and damn near everything else. And the one chance, the ONE chance we have to end this war, and maybe start a new life where we can forget all this, it gets an arrow through the back!
... Yes? I mean, yes I can! And frankly, I'm sick of it!
WHAT THE HELL HAPPENED?!
Sir, you can stop yelling. We can hear you.
Oh, right.
The bomb Perkins set off caused an avalanche.
And a bunch of deadly animals are stampeding straight toward us.
Thanks, Perkins. You've ruined all our lives. How do you feel about that?
Don't have to tell me three times!
I'd like to personally thank you in your assistance for helping with these stampeding animals.
Lieutenant Morgan!
You're… welcome?
As you can see, my troops are very busy in the midst of this unexpected and perfectly natural disaster. So busy, we wouldn't have time to pursue you if you so chose to abscond from a fight.
Not… really sure I'm following you.
Lieutenant, these animals could injure nearby townsfolk, and that is my top priority. I am simply too busy to engage you right now. And I think you should leave.
As in immediately.
Lieutenant, permission to take a short leave this afternoon.
Ramsey, we've talked about this, you're allowed to relax in the evening unless you're specifically on duty. You don't have to request leave.
Right, sorry, Morgan. I'm just feeling really run down and out of sorts. Wanted to make sure you could spare me.
Again, if you're not on the duty roster, I'm not sparing you, I already have things covered. Go relax. Take it easy.
Will do, Lieutenant. I'll probably just do a quick workout, get the blood pumping.
Just need some exercise equipment.
What's insane about a commitment to physical fitness?
I thought you were doing a quick workout. What's with the ball and chain?
Seriously?
I'm getting slow, Morgan! I can't let a little thing like a seventy pound weight around one ankle keep me from nailing a four minute mile!
Okay, right, see, I just forget sometimes that you are an insane person. So thank you for reminding me about that.
It's not enough, Zoey! I'm pushing myself as hard as I can, but I still can't shake this feeling. I've gotta work through it!

I've been tinkerin' with an idea: directly stimulatin' muscle groups with an electrical charge to force contractions. I kinda figured it would be for torture or somethin', but you could probably use it to work out longer.
I'm in! What do you need?
I can rig somethin' up with a couple of Electro-Geared Cutters from the Machine Shop.
If this doesn't kill him, he's gonna be in GREAT shape.
None of them made it back, though...
These are fantastic! I ran until I passed out, and then I just kept running! I woke up alone in the middle of the wasteland!
Zoey!
That's what kept happening to the test subjects too!
Your hunch mighta been right. That rover broke down just before reachin' the mountains. I ain't been able to get a signal.
Don't tell me you're thinking of going out there without assistance?
Findin' Dr. Harris might be the best chance we got at winnin' this war. I ain't gonna give up on that.
Well, we can't go with you, but I'll pull some strings and get you something to take along.
Why do mad inventors always gotta be the reclusive types?
Here's the rover. The poor thing got completely fried.
I think I just found out why…
I get a bit weirded out just talkin' to myself out here.
These traps are givin' me all sortsa ideas for the Outpost.
There's a cave been lived in, but Dr. Harris musta cleared out years ago.
There has to be something left behind. Some sort of clue. Harris ain't getting away that easy.
You've either gone insane and joined the Silverwolves, or you just really don't like me.
Silverwolves?
I wouldn't rule out either of those options yet.
They need a place to work. We thought they might be useful to you.
Suppose we could use some help in the mines. But I'd need some help in training them. You folks wouldn't mind?
I think I'm holding this pick-axe upside down?
We'll deal with the future when it comes.
Thanks for your help. They seem eager to work now, though I worry about what could happen in the future.
I feel a bit strange sending people into forced labor…
Ramsey, have you seen Perkins? He never got those blood stains out of my church pants.
Yeah, about that…
He's undercover in a Rebel camp in the Heartland, attempting to extract details on the mole who is compromising the security of the outpost or die trying.
Oh man, that little bastard better not die trying! I SPECIFICALLY told him not to die trying!
Morgan expresses his concern for Perkins… not… well.
Do you have ANY IDEA how SCARED I was?
Perkins! I have a really vivid memory where I told you not to do the thing you just did. I don't… I don't even…
I mean, you know how mad I get at you normally, can you imagine how angry I am with you when you're actively insubordinate?
I have details on a half dozen leaks, including two in Recoil Ridge, and a good twenty more solid leads.
Fine, you can come home, but you are in all KINDS of trouble, Mister.
Ah, Lieutenant Morgan! It's good to see you.
Woah! When did you get here?
Me? A little while ago. I understand that you've been distracted.
Man, you ain't kiddin'. What's up? Do you need like… some ropes? For… tying things?
Nothing so specific. Perhaps some hardtack for the road?
I mean, that's… most of what we make at the bakery. We can probably see to that.
Every knot was once straight rope.
Huh, I guess adventurous archeologists have surprisingly dynamic schedules.
Percival! Sorry, things have been nuts around here. So, what do you say, time to check out the textbooks? If they're for kids, we might even be able to understand them!
Alas, Perkins dear lad, now is not the time. I must make my way. Other opportunities await. But chin up, I'll return, and perhaps then we can make our attempt.
Oh, yeah, sure. I'll just… I'll see you then.
Sir, remember the time we paid off informants in Recoil Ridge?
Yes, and I will never let you forget the money we blew on that or the time spent building those persuaders.
I know I said I'd punish you, but frankly, I've been kind of busy, and it's just so embarrassing... I'd rather not make a huge deal out of it, you know?
Wow… okay...
Sir, I just saw Perkins looking defeated, wandering out of the Outpost? Do you know anything about that?
I heard nothing you said, Ramsey, because there is still blood on my church pants and I have something important to do in twenty minutes!
Wait, has anyone seen Perkins?
I am fairly certain there was not a Rebel camp here a few months ago.
This is probably not a good idea...
On it, LT!
So Floyd, is this mine empty, like that other one?
Well, given that it's not 500 years old and built by an unknown culture that seems to have developed well before any known, no, it's not like that other mine.
As for being empty, I don't believe so, but it's dangerous to spend much time deep in the mine without protection.
Wait, Floyd, are you asking me if you can borrow -
Hazmat suits Morgan. I'm going to make Hazmat suits.
Ok, cool, because like, the other things… they're not easy to get out here. And I need mine. All of them.
What in the world is he talking about?
That would be my supposition as well.
We've made a reasonably thorough examination of the mine. There is, to say the least, plenty of Uranium, given that we don't know what it does or how to use it. The mine looks nearly brand new.
Sweet! We're rich! Are we rich?
Rich in radioactive minerals, certainly. I'm not really sure how that translates to material wealth.
Huh. I'm gonna guess "badly."
So we don't know what Uranium is, or how to use it, but I feel like, you know, we've come this far… can we dig it up?
I've been working on that actually. We have most of the tools we need, and can fabricate what we don't have. We'll also need lead containers, as radiation shielding.
Man, this Uranium stuff better do something cool.
Wait, isn't lead toxic?
Does it have to do with Pyramids?
Well, we have a bunch of lead containers full of a radioactive material we don't understand.
On the plus side, we've completed the mission we were sent here for, by a government that no longer exists to support an army that has been defeated in a war we've already lost.
Morgan, are you familiar with the concept of a Pyrrhic Victory?
Morgan! I have some news about the mine!
What's with the smile? Did the Uranium turn useful or are we just finding gold or something now?
Hmm? Oh! No! This is bad news. Sorry, I'm in a good mood about unrelated events.  Anyway, the mine is under attack. Spiderwasps.
Man, you can't build a guy up like that.
My tomatoes are coming in!
I guess I give up sleeping for the rest of my life.
Well Morgan, we've done it! The mine is safe again!
Is there secret bad news you're not telling me?
Not… that I know of? It's always possible there's secret bad news none of us know. You might be secretly sick or something. There could be a meteor headed here to destroy us all.
Well… that's deeply upsetting.

It's amazing what the Reef Bandits can do without any safety regulations. With this facility, you can find out for yourself!
Reef Bandit Armory

Esta fábrica se encarga de llenarte de los cohetes que necesitas para convertir tu ejército en una fuerza mortal. Si, con el poder extremo de los delicados explosivos puedes convertir tu puesto en un cráter en cuestión de segundos pero bueno, si no te arriesgas...
Fábrica de cohetes

Una instalación ultra secreta para producir los mejores guerreros del imperio. En este edificio son formados los soldados más poderosos, mejor entrenados y más exclusivos. No serás un comandante de verdad hasta que no estés al frente de un mortal comando en el campo de batalla.
Operaciones especiales
Date el gusto de tener una Fábrica de armas. Vas a poder entrenar soldados en el uso de nuevo y poderoso armamento como la ametralladora pesada y la bazuca. Adelante. Te lo mereces.
Fábrica de armas
¿Qué mejor manera de dominarlo todo que dominarlo usando la propia naturaleza? ¡Es hora de que estas bestias aprendan a servirle al imperio!
Entrenador de animales

¡Mejora tu campo de entrenamiento! Descubre nuevas unidades y entrénalas más rápido usando menos recursos!

Usa los campos de entrenamiento para formar soldados.
Campos entrenamiento
¿Cansado de los debiluchos Pie grande? Si nos das los que tienes los convertiremos en máquinas de matar, ¡casi todos hacen lo que les ordenas!
Cuartel de Pie Grande

Upgrade the Dry Dock to unlock new boats and build them faster for less Gold and fewer Resources!

Far superior to all those other docks that aren't dry, you can construct ships here without all that pesky water getting in the way.
Dry Dock
Using the latest techniques in fish whispering, the technicians at this facility have finally learned how to train giant murderous fish to fight for you instead of against you!
Fish Hatchery

¡Cerveza gratis!

Consumir cerveza constituye un contrato con caracter vinculante entre el consumidor (de aquí en adelante, el tonto) y la armada imperial.
Reclutamiento fronterizo
Un simple pero preciso lente molido es el secreto detrás de la tecnología láser. La mayoría de gente que vive aquí hacía vasos con él.
Laboratorio óptico

Half of this factory's time is spent making plasma weapons. The other half is spent training the troopers and tank drivers to make sure they don't end up accidentally wiping out all life within a two mile radius.
Plasma Weapons Factory

Entrena tropas que no puedes conseguir de ninguna otra forma con las estrellas. Los soldados que salen del Campo de prestigio tienen mejores armas, mejores habilidades, los dientes más blancos y huelen mejor.
Campo de prestigio

Los asaltantes del santuario bajo el liderazgo del Mayor Taos no son precisamente muy amigables. Sin embargo el Señor Gantas se ha convertido en un dolor de cabeza para ellos. Si puedes mostrarles suficientes cráneos de asaltantes caídos en batalla, tal vez puedas convencerles que luchen por tí.
Entrenamiento asaltante
A los Lobos plateados les gusta el oro. Tú tienes oro. ¿Tal vez podamos llegar a un arreglo?
Bóveda mercenaria

¡Mejora tu fábrica de vehículos! Descubre los nuevos y constrúyelos más rápido usando menos recursos

Demuestra tus verdaderas habilidades bélicas creando tu fábrica de vehículos. Construye poderosos lanzacohetes, buggies y sobre todo ¡TANQUES! Una cosa, ¡necesitarás petróleo!
Fábrica de vehículos

¡Mejora y reduce el tiempo de curación y su costo en oro y recursos además de aumentar la lista de espera!

¡Mejora, reduce el tiempo de curación, su costo en oro, recursos y aumenta la lista de espera!

Primero reemplazamos a los humanos por robots; enseguida las máquinas se sublevan y luchan contra sus amos hasta la muerte. Por último le damos los trabajos a los seres humanos que sobreviven. Es así como reducimos los costes... de alguna manera.
Muelle de rep. avanzado
El dinero mueve el mundo, ¿pero sabes qué más lo mueve? La energía. Esta nueva planta producirá aún más energía lo que significa mejores edificios.

¡Mejora y aumenta la producción de cemento!

¡Mejora para aumentar tu producción!

Milagros de la tecnología moderna: este molino convierte la piedra en... ¡cemento!

Al aumentar peligrosamente el número de sierras en el lugar de trabajo, tus empleados estarán asustados aumentando así la producción y la eficiencia. ¡Con el aserradero avanzado obtendrás el doble de madera al día con la misma cantidad de empleados!

¿Te gustaría convertir la madera en tablones? ¡Pues para eso sirven los aserraderos, hombre!

Normally, adding oil to chemicals just gives you oily chemicals, but a top secret process fuses the two into valuable plasma. Just be sure to read the 500 page safety manual before getting within fifty feet of a single drop.

¡Mejora y aumenta la producción de acero!

¡Mejora para aumentar la producción de carbón!

¡Mejora para aumentar la producción de carbón!

¡Mejora para aumentar la producción de hierro!

¡Mejora para aumentar la producción de hierro!

La inversión del imperio para desarrollar una excavadora gigante y más aguda ¡por fin ha dado frutos! ¡Tenemos el placer de presentar la Ventoexcavadora, un gigantesco taladro extra afiliado con el cual podrás duplicar la producción de hierro!
Mina de Hierro mod.

¡Mejora para aumentar la producción de petróleo!

Cantera mod.

Campo maderero mod.

Fun? The bar is understocked, the bathrooms aren't up to code, and someone let their pet raptor loose in the halls. How do you EXPECT ME TO HAVE FUN?

¡Creemos que la mejor idea es deshacernos de todas las sombras! Si creamos una serie de espejos y los ubicamos alrededor de nuestro puesto podríamos reflectar la luz por todo el sitio. ¡Adiós a la oscuridad!

… una distracción.

Como lo has señalado, usan muchos cuchillos y al parecer los hacen ellos mismos. Sus metalurgias necesitan mucho combustible, asi que si cortamos su fuente de suministro, les dañaremos la producción de armas.

que encontraran una mujer formidable. Una que tuviera una belleza por encima de la de las demás. Ellos la encontraron.

queréis desafiarme? Es que es absurdo. ¡Ni siquiera sé quien es ella!

pero los demás han fracasado en su intento.

¡Perkins!
¡Bestia raquítica! ¡Hasta aquí llega tu vida!
No eres Perkins.
¡Tengo la forma de tu muerte!
Cuando era un chico, una anciana de la montaña me dijo que mi muerte tenía algo de equina.
¡La anciana de la montaña no sabe nada!

¿Ves? Te has equivocado de montura. Supuestamente en mi destino, mi muerte tiene algo que ver con caballos.
¡Entonces iré a buscar unos caballos y ya regreso por ti!
No, no lo hagas.
Imperial, busco a ese que se hace llamar Morgan y bestia raquítica.
¡Morgan! ¡Ha llegado otro de esos asaltantes que quiere matarte!
Confundes mis intenciones pequeño. No es por Yenkcha que vengo, estoy felizmente comprometido. Quiero hacerle una oferta a Morgan.
Si no son del estilo "balas en mi cuerpo", te escucho.

Tu leyenda sigue subiendo y más de mis hermanos vendrán a retarte. Quiero construir un lugar de descanso en esa ruta que ellos toman. Allí podré vender comida y agua  a esos que quieren ganarse la mano de Yenkcha.
¿Qué necesitas de mi?
Necesito unas provisiones y recursos para comenzar esta empresa. Si me ayudas compartiré mis ganancias contigo.
Al fin, ¡ser el mejor en todo tiene su ganancia!
Pueden ir al lago que tenemos. ¡A nadar!
¡A nuestra empresa!
¡Asi es! ¡Espero que la gente de mi tribu te siga cazando sin cesar!
¡Eso no importa! Pueden seguir viniendo a saludarme o a lo que sea.
La bestia raquítica será…
¡Morgan! Uno de esos vagos ha venido a dispararte.
Que ingenuo.  Yenkcha no le daría a un vago ninguna oportunidad.
Asi es. Incluso de llegar a superarte, en el sistema de clases de los asaltantes un vago será siempre un vago… aunque claro, hay cosas que se escapan a nuestro entendimiento..
¡Os recuerdo que os estoy escuchando!
Cierto. Vamos a dispararte para que Floyd y yo podamos terminar nuestra conversación.

Preferiría que no me dispararas una vez mas.
Has luchado bien Bestia raquítica. Ya veo porque Yenkcha…
Digamos que mi pistola no funcione o algo y yo acabe derrotado. De ninguna forma Yenkcha se va a casar con él. Algún otro asaltante acabaría con él al día siguiente.
No creo que…
No puedo impedir pensar que al ser tú derrotado por alguien de inferior estatus, no solo dañe tu imagen sino también la de Yenkcha…

Por favor, que los mayores estamos hablando.
Y por mi cumpleaños todo lo que deseo es un regalo que os una e inspire a todos y cada uno de vosotros: ¡una estatua gigante de mi persona!
Le he preguntado al Alto Mando con cuánta piedra tendrá que contribuir cada ciudad y puesto avanzado para tan noble esfuerzo.
Mis vagos ciudadanos. Hoy cumplo 26 años y medio.
A ver si conseguimos enviar la piedra más rápido que nadie. No quiero que el Alto Mando se olvide de mí. Digo, de nosotros. Incluso contribuiré a la causa con nanopods.
Es nuestra oportunidad de destacar.
Cuando tengas suficiente piedra, toca el botón "Dar" de esta ventana para completar el objetivo.
¡Hemos batido un récord! Y a juzgar por la recompensa, el Alto Mando se ha dado cuenta de nuestros esfuerzos. El emperador es un tío estupendo...
¡Recibo una señal de la capital!

Mis eufémicos ciudadanos... mientras el 2º y 5º regimiento del ejército imperial avanzan hacia el sureste donde la actividad rebelde es más intensa, nosotros vamos a celebrarlo en su honor. ¡El Imperio dará un gran banquete!

Y para financiar un banquete del tamaño y envergadura que merecen estos valientes muchachos, el Imperio solicita a todos sus leales ciudadanos que compartan lo que puedan para sostener nuestras reservas.

Aunque es muy seguro que desgraciadamente los corajudos hombres por los que celebramos la fiesta no estén presentes físicamente, hemos contratado a los mejores fotógrafos de banquetes para que se lleven un buen recuerdo.
Me hace sentir un calorcillo y cierta confusión.
La ginebra.
¿Sabes lo que me hace sentir eso a mí?
Habrá que construir más granjas.
Espero que no se ponga malo. Como la mano de Buda se pudra, el Alto Mando no nos va a tener en mucha estima.
¡Recibo una señal del Imperio!
Como sabéis, en todo el Imperio tenemos cientos de proyectos de investigación para dar con nuevas y gloriosas formas de aplastar a los rebeldes.

Nuestro proyecto secreto de Blackish Butte ha tenido TAL éxito que hemos decidido poner freno a su progreso. La "descongestión cuantitativa" se realizará con una combinación de enorme pilas de madera y varios galones de líquido más ligero.
Gracias de nuevo por vuestro servicio incondicional y por no acercaos a 160 kilómetros de Blackish Butte hasta nuevo aviso.
¡Saludos, mis insolubles ciudadanos!
Yo siempre digo: tened paciencia. O usad nanopods. Bueno, ya sabéis.
Espera... la dirección de envío pone "A/a: Operaciones de recuperación científica imperial." ¿No es allí donde está destinada...? En fin, da igual.
¡Eh, el emperador vuelve a hablar por la radio!
¡Saludos, mis obtusos súbditos! La República de Kalakuri ha erigido un pilar de hierro de 120 metros. Súbditos, sé lo que estáis pensando, pero ahí va: ¡debemos construir una columna de 121 metros!
¡Todos debéis contribuir al esfuerzo! Yo mismo contrataré al equipo de diseño y elegiré la forma de la columna. Vosotros entregaréis el hierro necesario para construirlo.
Será duro, pero el orgullo de la República se convertirá en vergüenza cuando observen con envidia nuestro férreo monumento. Estas órdenes deberán realizarse con la mayor premura.

Si nos hacemos a ese puesto de forma silenciosa, vamos a poder ingresar al pueblo y acabar con el trabajo antes de que se den cuenta qué los ha golpeado. Usé esa misma estrategia en la batalla de Magnessan.

Atalaya rebelde

Perkins sigue llorando sobre su necesidad de atacar a los rebeldes. Alega que su amigo se encuentra ahora mismo luchando por su vida. ¿Qué es lo que está pasando? No sabía que el chico tuviese amigos.

Perkins se hizo amigo del saboteador imperial con quien lo hemos dejado. Tenemos que regresar para darle apoyo con el resto de nuestro ejército y destruir el puesto rebelde.

¡A tu rescate amigo!
¿Dónde está la manguera?

Misión cumplida señor.
¡No puedo encontrar a mi amigo por ningún lado! ¿Y si lo han capturado? ¡Tendré que cubrir mi rostro con lodo para infiltrarme y liberarlo!

Cálmate Perkins.
Si ha quedado alguno, pasamos dos veces por el camino y cubrimos nuestras huellas. No van a poder encontrar nuestro puesto.
¡Perkins! ¡Te ordené ir por esas provisiones hace media hora! ¿Qué haces todavía aquí?

¡Pues levántalos con tus piernas, no con tu espalda! ¿Es que tengo que pensar en todo?

¡Alguien le ha disparado a mi copa de brandy cuando la tenía en mi mano!

¡Ya sé porqué tenemos tantas ruedas pinchadas! ¡Vamos a por el francotirador antes de que se escape!
¡Era mi copa preferida!
¡El disparo proviene de esa colina!
¡Mi casco saltó solo!
¡Nos está disparando! Tenemos que llegar a él antes que nos fríe a todos.
¡Era mi copa preferida!
Por favor que no me vea, por favor que no me vea…
¡Se escapa!, ¡a por él!
¡Espera! Si todos vamos tras él quien sabe qué nos tenga preparado. Lo mejor es enviar un pequeño grupo para que lo siga hasta su escondite.

Señor, los exploradores nos informan que las torres de guardia de Sarin se encuentran ocupadas en su totalidad.

¡Tanques!
¡No entenderías!
¡Seguro que no todos vosotros sois unos cobardicas! Vuestro coraje es admirable aunque me río de vuestra idiotez al no rendiros mientras podíais hacerlo.

¡Lo mejor es que los edificios tienen muchísimas menos astillas!

Miedo.

Aquí tienes. Te has ganado el señuelo que nuestros cazadores siempre llevan consigo. Los gusanos siempre irán a por ellos, incluso en tierras imperiales.
Espera. ¿Ya tenías el señuelo? Pero si arriesgué mi vida con esos muñecos de prueba...

Ya está. He terminado los planos para una trampa túnel de puerta inversa de una sola vía para los gusanos de arena. Es como una trampa para cangrejos que se ancla a sí misma bajo varios centímetros de tierra. Que empiece la producción.
¡Pero si acabamos de llegar! ¿Cómo lo hiciste?

¡Es por eso que estamos en la cima de la cadena alimenticia!

Oops.

¡Claro! ¡Bien!

¡Sin escudo! ¡Entendido!

Intentar... apuntar... Genial. ¡Gracias por la ayuda!
No me importaría volver a ver a ese chico Ramsey por estos lares.
Si el soldado se preparase un poco más, ¡no estaría a punto de caerse casi siempre!

uno de los pueblos fronterizos… ¿cuál era?

su líder esta furioso ya que las fuerzas imperiales se están aprovechando del dinero recaudado de la estafa que los Lobos plateados tenían montada.
sus chicos que les "enseñe a esos bastardos imperiales quien domina el norte".

¡Pretendientes!

¡Todo el mundo listo!

pero no me gusta la idea de tener una fábrica de esclavos.
